*Last call for ICPRAI <https://icprai2022.sciencesconf.org/>'2022=20
Doctoral Consortium - DL Extension*

/ICPRAI 2022 - 3rd International Conference on Pattern Recognition and=20
Artificial Intelligence//
//Doctoral consortium: May 31, 2022//
//Paris (France)/

/https://easychair.org/my/conference?conf=3Dicprai2022/

This year, the steering committee of ICPRAI 2022 proposes the first=20
version of the Doctoral Consortium (DC) as a satellite event to the main=20
conference offering the opportunit=C3=A9 to PhD students to present their=
=20
work and meet senior researchers in their feld of interest.

The goal of the ICPRAI 2022 Doctoral Consortium is to create an=20
opportunity for Ph.D. students to test their research ideas, present=20
their current progress and future plans, and receive constructive=20
criticism and insights related to their future work and career=20
perspectives. A mentor (a senior researcher who is active in the field)=20
will be assigned to each student to provide individual feedback. In=20
addition, students will have the opportunity to present an overview of=20
their research plan during a special poster session.

Participation in the ICPRAI 2022 Doctoral Consortium will be limited to=20
25 students. Prospective participants are encouraged to submit their=20
application. The Doctoral Consortium Committee will then review all=20
applications received. Preference will be given to students who are at a=20
stage in their studies most likely to benefit (i.e., they have=20
identified a research direction and published some initial results, but=20
the thesis is not yet set in stone).

------------------------------------------------------------------------
*Submission procedure*

Students willing to participate should submit a participation package in=20
a single pdf file. The submission package should be prepared using the=20
following templates and should contain the following information:

  * Student=E2=80=99s name
  * University
  * Title of your thesis
  * Supervisor of the thesis
  * Starting and expected finalization date of the PhD
  * Short research plan (1-2 pages about the work)
  * Short CV (1-2 pages).

The research plan should contain an overview of the PhD topic relative=20
to the topics of the main conference, the steps made so far (including a=20
list of publications), and the actions planned before finishing the PhD,=20
especially novel research ideas to be pursued.

Submission should be done before February 1st, 2022 via easychair=20
<https://easychair.org/my/conference?conf=3Dicprai2022> (select Track=20
"ICPRAI 2022 - Doctoral Consortium") :

------------------------------------------------------------------------

*Important dates*

  * Submission deadline: February 15, 2022
  * Acceptance notification and mentor assignment: February 21th, 2022
  * Mentoring starting period: February 25th, 2022
  * Final material due: May 20th, 2022
  * Doctoral Consortium: May 31st, 2022

------------------------------------------------------------------------

*Registration
*

Participation to the Doctoral Consortium will be free for all accepted=20
students, i.e., there will be no extra registration fees! The ICPRAI=20
2022 Doctoral Consortium will take place the day before the main=20
conference, i.e., on May 31st.

Veronique Eglin, Daniel Lopresti
Doctoral Consortium Chairs

--=20
V=C3=A9ronique Eglin
Directrice adjointe du LIRIS - UMR 5205 CNRS
INSA Lyon

